    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-10T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-10T05:00:00-05:00" n="105"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5785</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WP1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wheeler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-10T19:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 10, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 12.43 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MIV1">Viscount Motono</persName> unofficially asks me to
                    let you know that if it is convenient and agreeable for <persName
                        corresp="#p_RE1">Root</persName> and his party to visit Japan on the way
                    back to the United States it would be a gratification to both the people and the
                    Government of Japan. Personally he expressed a very keen hope that this could be
                    arranged. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_RE1">Root</persName>’s party are expected to
                    arrive Vladivostok 17th instant.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WP1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wheeler</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
